Hi there,<br /><br />I've been looking around the internet for a start menu application for my Windows 8 OS. <br /><br />I've used Classic Shell before and I love the program but on my search I found a few interesting features that Classic Shell could maybe incorporate. <br /><br />- Grouping Programs<br /><br />Organizing programs into different groups on the start menu. Groups by criteria such as: Games, Utilities, Programming, Video, Music, System, Internet. <br />Perhaps even making the groups collapsible would be a great idea.<br /><br />- Single Click Open<br /><br />Opening programs in folders by a single click. As in click on the Microsoft Word folder and it opens the main application by linking the executable to the folder.<br /><br />- Power Options<br /><br />Simple options for power buttons like: Force Shutdown, timer shutdown, remote shutdown.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=671">priestfeast</a> — Sat Apr 27, 2013 9:53 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
